> **NOTE:** Available in v1.135.0+.

{{< chooser language "typescript,python,go,csharp" / >}}





{{< example csharp >}}

```csharp
using Pulumi;
using AliCloud = Pulumi.AliCloud;

class MyStack : Stack
{
    public MyStack()
    {
        var ids = Output.Create(AliCloud.BastionHost.GetHosts.InvokeAsync(new AliCloud.BastionHost.GetHostsArgs
        {
            InstanceId = "example_value",
            Ids = 
            {
                "1",
                "2",
            },
        }));
        this.BastionhostHostId1 = ids.Apply(ids => ids.Hosts[0].Id);
        var nameRegex = Output.Create(AliCloud.BastionHost.GetHosts.InvokeAsync(new AliCloud.BastionHost.GetHostsArgs
        {
            InstanceId = "example_value",
            NameRegex = "^my-Host",
        }));
        this.BastionhostHostId2 = nameRegex.Apply(nameRegex => nameRegex.Hosts[0].Id);
    }

    [Output("bastionhostHostId1")]
    public Output<string> BastionhostHostId1 { get; set; }
    [Output("bastionhostHostId2")]
    public Output<string> BastionhostHostId2 { get; set; }
}
```

{{< example go >}}

```go
package main

import (
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi-alicloud/sdk/v3/go/alicloud/bastionhost"
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi/sdk/v3/go/pulumi"
)

func main() {
	pulumi.Run(func(ctx *pulumi.Context) error {
		ids, err := bastionhost.GetHosts(ctx, &bastionhost.GetHostsArgs{
			InstanceId: "example_value",
			Ids: []string{
				"1",
				"2",
			},
		}, nil)
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		ctx.Export("bastionhostHostId1", ids.Hosts[0].Id)
		opt0 := "^my-Host"
		nameRegex, err := bastionhost.GetHosts(ctx, &bastionhost.GetHostsArgs{
			InstanceId: "example_value",
			NameRegex:  &opt0,
		}, nil)
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		ctx.Export("bastionhostHostId2", nameRegex.Hosts[0].Id)
		return nil
	})
}
```
